post_text:
GATES MILLS ELEMENTARY RAISES $1,083 FOR THE LEUKEMIA & LYMPHOMA SOCIETY

Gates Mills Elementary School had an amazing year supporting The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society through Pennies for Patients!

Erin Zaranec, Campaign Manager for the Leukemia & Lymphoma Society recognized Gates Mills Elementary Principal Laurel Ravida, students and staff for their ongoing support of the Pennies for Patients program.

‚ÄúUnder the leadership of Laurel Ravida, the school raised $1,083 for The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society ‚Äì funds that will assist not only patients in Northern Ohio, but across the nation. The last time the school participated was the 2016-2017 school year, when they raised $662, The students were absolutely amazing during our kick-off assembly and it was inspiring to see Laurel‚Äôs dedication to the cause," Ms. Zaranac said.

MMS AND LANDER ELEMENTARY NAMED CLEVELAND CLINIC BANNER SCHOOLS: Mayfield Middle School AND Lander Elementary have been named a Cleveland Clinic Banner School. The following letter was received by MMS Principal Destino and Lander Elementary Principal Felecia Evans from the Clinic. #mychoicemayfield #mayfieldtogether

"This year has posed unprecedented challenges to educational organizations across the country and around the world. The resolve, ingenuity, and adaptability you have shown in response to COVID-19 were evident long before this pandemic, however, and have distinguished Mayfield Middle School as a 2019‚Äì2020 Cleveland Clinic Banner School. This award recognizes your noteworthy success in leveraging community resources to advance student learning."

March 17, 2020
Dear Mayfield administrators, teachers, staff, parents, students and community,
On behalf of the Mayfield Board of Education, I want to thank every one of you for your strength, patience and adaptation during this unprecedented time in our world, in our nation and in our schools.
The coronavirus pandemic is a reality that is changing every day and hour by hour.
The decision by Ohio Governor Mike DeWine to close all Ohio school facilities, restaurants, bars and theaters, along with the declaration to postpone Ohio‚Äôs primary election today, signifies the critical importance to slow the spread of this novel virus.

SCIENCE SHOWCASE CANCELLED
A Letter from Superintendent Keith Kelly

Dear Mayfield teachers, staff, parents and community,
Today, Ohio Governor Mike DeWine and the Ohio Department of Health issued a recommendation to limit all large, public events to help slow the spread of COVID-19 in Ohio.
Based on this information, Mayfield City Schools is cancelling the annual Science Showcase scheduled for tomorrow evening March 11, 2020 from 6-7:30 p.m. at Mayfield High School.
The Science Showcase typically draws 1,500 guests. The Showcase is a well-attended, close-contact, district-sponsored event for students in Kindergarten through Grade 12 held throughout the high school in classrooms, hallways,‚Ä¶ More
text:
SCIENCE SHOWCASE CANCELLED
A Letter from Superintendent Keith Kelly

Dear Mayfield teachers, staff, parents and community,
Today, Ohio Governor Mike DeWine and the Ohio Department of Health issued a recommendation to limit all large, public events to help slow the spread of COVID-19 in Ohio.
Based on this information, Mayfield City Schools is cancelling the annual Science Showcase scheduled for tomorrow evening March 11, 2020 from 6-7:30 p.m. at Mayfield High School.
The Science Showcase typically draws 1,500 guests. The Showcase is a well-attended, close-contact, district-sponsored event for students in Kindergarten through Grade 12 held throughout the high school in classrooms, hallways,‚Ä¶ More

post_text: COMMUNITY ASSET: When we combine education, training, life skills and community partnership, it's a win-win for the students, teachers and community. That's the Excel TECC Cosmetology program in a nutshell. It was a very busy Friday at the Cosmetology Salon today in Highland Heights with students orchestrating a full client schedule of services like hair cuts, manicures, pedicures and preparation for the State cosmetology exam in May. Mayfield Heights resident Lydia Butler said, "This is a great community partnership. When we support this program, we're not only getting a great service, like a haircut, but we're helping the student to learn." #mychoicemayfield #allaccesslearning

CLEVELAND.COM

post_text: PRESERVING OUR HISTORY: Mayfield City Schools, Gates Mills Village and the Gates Mills Historical Society celebrated the 50th anniversary of the United States Coast Guard Station which was located on the grounds of the Gates Mills Environmental Education Center from 1941-1969. The commemorative event was attended today by more than 50 guests, including four representatives from the U.S. Coast Guard 9th Division. A plaque explaining the historical significance of the station was unveiled at the entrance of the of the Environmental Education Center, 390 County Line Road. According to history, the U.S. Coast Guard Station was located there as it is the highest elevation in Cuyahoga County. When the station closed, the property was deeded to the Mayfield City School District which has operated the Excel TECC/Gates Mills Environmental Education Center there ever since. #mychoicemayfield #allaccesslearning

Presale tickets for the playoff football game at home on Friday, November 8th are available for sale online only from through 4:00 PM on 11/8. This is a new procedure implemented by the OHSAA. The school selected at checkout will receive a percentage of presale revenue. Go to www.ohsaa.org/tickets to purchase presale tickets and skip the lines at the stadium. Since this is an OHSAA playoff game, no passes or discounts can be offered and all seats at Wildcat Stadium will be general admission. Specific reserved section tickets will not be sold. The school selected at checkout will receive a percentage of presale revenue. Go to www.ohsaa.org/tickets to purchase presale tickets and skip the lines at the stadium. Since this is an OHSAA playoff game, no passes or discounts can be offered and all seats at Wildcat Stadium will be general admission. Specific reserved section tickets will not be sold. Contact the Mayfield Athletic Office at (440) 995-6830 with any questions.
